Shrimp Scampi

2 tbsp evoo
1 lb (21-25) shrimp, peeled and deveined
3 garlic cloves, minced
2 large plum tomatoes, peeled, seeded, and diced
2 tbsp lemon juice
2 tbsp vermouth or dry white wine
2 tbsp unsalted butter cut into 4 pieces
2 tbsp finely chopped parsley
kosher salt
fresh ground black pepper

Heat the oil in a large skillet or saute pan over medium heat until it shimmers, 1-2 min, then add the shrimp. Cook, stirring often, until the shrimp start to curl and turn pink, 1- 1/2 min. Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~30 sec, then add the tomatoes and cook for 30 s more. Turn off the heat and stir in the lemon juice and vermouth. Add the butter, stirring until it melts. Stir in 1 tbsp of the parsley and season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle the remaining parsley over the top and serve.
